President Muhammadu Buhari on Thursday arrived in Sokoto State and met with Governor Aminu Tambuwal over the recent killings in the state. Buhari is expected to proceed to Zamfara State to commiserate and condole with the governor of the state, Bello Matawalle on various cases of insecurities recorded in the state especially the recent terrorist attacks in Anka and Bukkuyum Local Government Areas where many people were killed.  SaharaReporters on Wednesday reported that Matawalle confirmed that, “All is set to ensure the president is received successfully.” “I want to inform all the good people of Zamfara State that the Commander in Chief of the Federal Republic of Nigeria will come to Zamfara on Thursday specifically for a condolence visit over the recent bandits’ attacks in Anka and Bukkuyum Local Government Areas of the state.” He had also urged the entire people of the state to remain law-abiding during the President’s visit. Meanwhile, in a video online, President Buhari was seen as he arrived in Sokoto State to commiserate with the people. 